Defect 1 — bugSummary projects "priority" (always empty on disk) rather
than "severity".  The summary keys returned to consumers include
priority:"" and no severity key.

Defect 2 — listAllBugs sorts by BugFile.ID ASC.  Because IDs are
ISO-timestamp prefixed, this is effectively filed_at ASC; severity has
zero weight in the comparator.

Both failures match the two issues called out in the bug report.

(On HEAD, with the fix from commit f6c1ad3 applied, the same tests
PASS — confirming the test set is well-calibrated to the defect.)
